Paper: hep-th/0208040

Date: 2002-08-06

Title: Wigner's Formulation of Noncommutative Quantum Mechanics

Authors: Akira Kokado, Takashi Okamura, Takesi Saito

Comments: 10 pages, No figures, Latex

When we have noncommutativity among coordinates (or conjugate momenta), weconsider Wigner's formulation of quantum mechanics, including a new derivationof path integral formula. We also propose the Moyal star product based on theDirac bracket in constrained systems.